               <n2016:NUTS CODE="NO053"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Hjelset.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>A project office has been established at Hjelset for the SNR project. The project office's street address is Oppdølveien 14. The building, which is called “Strandheim”, is located on the eastern side of the site area for the new hospital. The building is from 1970 and it was originally built as a bedsit building for employees at the psychiatric hospital. The building was later used as a school. In 2015, the ground floor had minor alterations so that it could be used as a project office for the introductory phase. The building has 3 floors over a basement floor. In order to make room for the project organisation and accompanying activities, the upper 2 floors shall also be altered and upgraded. The 2 floors have a gross floor area of 600 m<FT TYPE="SUP">2</FT> (300 m<FT TYPE="SUP">2</FT> on each floor). In addition to the construction work, balanced ventilation and a lift shall be installed. The building shall be given a relatively general design as an office building, with the aim that, after the project organisation for SNR has moved out, it can still be used as offices.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
